#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police are investigating the cause of the fatal Limpopo bush crash which claimed 21 lives. Scores of people have also been left injured. The province's transport and community safety MEC Florence Radzilani says most of the patients have already been discharged, while others are still in critical condition. READ:Â Death toll in Limpopo bus crash rises to 21 The head-on collision happened on Monday between the bus and a cash-in-transit van. It's reported the bus rolled off a bridge into a river after the collision with the van. President Cyril Ramaphosa has offered his condolences to the families of the 21 people who died in the collision.